      • getMatching

        public Collection<com.giannoules.proxstor.api.Environmental> getMatching(com.giannoules.proxstor.api.Environmental partial)
        Find and returns all matching environmentals based on partially specified Environmental

        If the partially specified environmental includes a environmentalId field then that one property is used to match. If the environmentalId is not present, then all other properties are used using a GraphQuery to match. This means passing in a environmentalId will allow you to retrieve a specific environmental and bypass the normal requirement that environmental retrieval requires knowledge of the location containing it.

        Note that no exceptions are thrown. An invalid environmentalId is handled a simply a null response.

        Parameters:
        partial - Partially completed Environmental object
        Returns:
        Collection of Environmental objects matching partial, or null if none

      • update

        public boolean update(String locId,
             com.giannoules.proxstor.api.Environmental e)
               throws EnvironmentalNotContainedWithinLocation,
                      InvalidEnvironmentalId,
                      InvalidLocationId
        Updates (modifies) an existing environmental in the database. The environmental must be in a 'Within' relationship with the Location. All fields from the Environmental parameter will overwrite the fields of the original Environmental. The environmental id will remain the same.
        Parameters:
        locId - String representation of the Location containing the environmental
        e - Updated Environmental object
        Returns:
        true if the update was successful; false if a database error was encountered
        Throws:
        InvalidLocationId - If the locId parameter does not represent a valid location
        InvalidEnvironmentalId - If the dnvironmentalId within the s parameter does not represent a valid environmental
        EnvironmentalNotContainedWithinLocation - If the d.environmentalId and locId are valid, but the environmental is not within the location.

      • delete

        public boolean delete(String locId,
             String environmentalId)
               throws InvalidEnvironmentalId,
                      InvalidLocationId,
                      EnvironmentalNotContainedWithinLocation
        Remove a Environmental from the database. The location must have a 'within' relationship to the environmental for the operation to succeed.
        Parameters:
        locId - String representation of the location id containing the environmental
        environmentalId - String representation of the environmental to be removed
        Returns:
        true if the operation succeeds; false if communication error to the database
        Throws:
        InvalidEnvironmentalId - If environmentalId parameter is not a valid environmental in the graph
        InvalidLocationId - If locId parameter is not a valid location in the graph
        EnvironmentalNotContainedWithinLocation - If the locId and environmentalId are valid, but the environmental is not within the location.
